{
  "id": "medium_01_js",
  "title": "Event Dispatcher (JS)",
  "difficulty": "medium",
  "category": "Closure / late binding",
  "description": "You are building an event processing pipeline. Given a list of events, each with a `\"type\"` and a `\"payload\"`, route each event through its matching handler and return the results in order.\n\nEach result must be: `{\"event\": <type>, \"data\": <payload>}`\n\n**Example 1:**\nInput:\n```\nevents = [\n  {\"type\": \"login\",  \"payload\": \"user_123\"},\n  {\"type\": \"logout\", \"payload\": \"user_456\"}\n]\n```\nOutput:\n```\n[{\"event\": \"login\",  \"data\": \"user_123\"},\n {\"event\": \"logout\", \"data\": \"user_456\"}]\n```\n\n**Example 2:**\nInput: `[{\"type\": \"click\", \"payload\": \"btn_ok\"}, {\"type\": \"hover\", \"payload\": \"menu\"}]`\nOutput: `[{\"event\": \"click\", \"data\": \"btn_ok\"}, {\"event\": \"hover\", \"data\": \"menu\"}]`\n\n**Constraints:**\n- `1 <= len(events) <= 100`\n- Every event has exactly `\"type\"` (str) and `\"payload\"` (any) fields.\n\n**Note:** Handlers are built in a loop — pay close attention to how the loop variable is declared and how that affects the closures created inside it.",
  "files": [
    {
      "name": "main.js",
      "editable": true
    },
    {
      "name": "dispatcher.js",
      "editable": true
    }
  ],
  "entry_module": "main",
  "entry_function": "processEvents",
  "test_cases": [
    {
      "args": [
        [
          {
            "type": "login",
            "payload": "user_123"
          },
          {
            "type": "logout",
            "payload": "user_456"
          },
          {
            "type": "login",
            "payload": "user_789"
          }
        ]
      ],
      "expected": [
        {
          "event": "login",
          "data": "user_123"
        },
        {
          "event": "logout",
          "data": "user_456"
        },
        {
          "event": "login",
          "data": "user_789"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "args": [
        [
          {
            "type": "click",
            "payload": "btn_ok"
          },
          {
            "type": "hover",
            "payload": "menu_item"
          },
          {
            "type": "click",
            "payload": "btn_cancel"
          }
        ]
      ],
      "expected": [
        {
          "event": "click",
          "data": "btn_ok"
        },
        {
          "event": "hover",
          "data": "menu_item"
        },
        {
          "event": "click",
          "data": "btn_cancel"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "hint": "What's the difference between `var` and `let` inside a `for...of` loop when creating closures? By the time the arrow functions are called, what is `event`?",
